Data Mining Module Description

In this module, you will learn the basic concepts of data mining. You will gain skills in recognizing data mining problems, writing code, and an understanding of the importance of legal/ethical aspects of data mining.

Objectives

1. Describe the process of data mining and all phases in the process.

2. Explain the characteristics of raw data, and the techniques of preparing data for data mining methodologies.

3. Compare different predictive and descriptive data mining techniques.

4. Describe the practical considerations for developing data mining models.

5. Describe the legal, ethical, privacy, and security considerations associated with real world data and data mining models.

To Dos

1. Complete the Learning Module.

2. Complete the Homework Assignments (#1 and #2).

3. Complete the Survey.

4. Complete the Final Module Summative Assessment.
